Package: motifr
Title: Motif Analysis in Multi-Level Networks
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: 
    c(person(given = "Mario",
             family = "Angst",
             role = c("aut", "cre"),
             email = "mario.angst@wsl.ch",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8297-9827")),
      person(given = "Tim",
             family = "Seppelt",
             role = "aut",
             email = "t.seppelt@posteo.de",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6447-0568")))
Description: This package provides tools for motif analysis
    in multi-level networks. Multi-level networks combine multiple
    networks in one, e.g. social-ecological networks. Motifs are small
    configurations of nodes and edges (subgraphs) occurring in networks.
    motifr can visualize multi-level networks, count multi-level network
    motifs and compare motif occurences to baseline models. It also identifies contributions
    of existing or potential edges to motifs to find critical or missing edges.  The
    package is in many parts a R wrapper for the excellent
    'SESMotifAnalyser' Python package written by Tim Seppelt.
